! How To Create Your Own Obsidian Plugin - Step By Step

!! Abstract

Obsidian is a powerful note taking app. And it's actually possible to extend the features of Obsidian by writing your own plugins. This is a step by step guide, which shows you how to create and publish your own Obsidian plugins from scratch.
!! Requirements

* [[Obsidian|https://obsidian.md]]
* [[Git|https://git-scm.com]]
* [[GitHub|https://github.com]] account
* [[Node.js|https://nodejs.org]]
* Code Editor (I recommend [[VSCode|https://code.visualstudio.com]])
* Basic [[TypeScript|https://www.typescriptlang.org]] knowledge
!! Installing the sample plugin

* Login to Github
* Go to https://github.com/obsidianmd/obsidian-sample-plugin
* Use this template -> Select a new name, e.g. "Zeilencounter" -> Generates e.g. https://github.com/joka63/Zeilencounter
* `cd .obsidian/plugins`
* `git clone https://github.com/joka63/Zeilencounter.git`
* Zugriff auf private Repos nur mit [[Github Access Token|https://github.com/settings/tokens/new]], nicht mit Passwort!
* `cd Zeilencounter`
* `npm install`
** installs all dependencies, defined in `package.json` into a folder `node_modules`.
* `npm run dev`
** compiles Typescript code to ~JavaScript into `main.js` and watches for code changes.
** In Obsidian, press `Ctrl + P` and select `Reload app without saving`, in German: `Anwendung neuladen ohne zu speichern`.
* In Obsidian, go to settings -> Community plugins -> Enable "Example Plugin"
* Edit `manifest.json`
* Clear and edit `main.json` from scratch: 
```typescript
import { Plugin } from 'obsidian';

export default class ZeilencounterPlugin extends Plugin {
	async onload() {
		console.log('loading plugin Zeilencounter');
	}
}
```

!! Implementing a simple plugin
The sample plugin should add a line counter to Obsidian's standard status bar, counting words and characters.

When the plugin gets loaded, register a callback to the event `active-leaf-change` when a note is opened:

```typescript
export default class ZeilencounterPlugin extends Plugin {
	statusBarTextElement: HTMLSpanElement;

	/**
	 * Called when the plugin is loaded
	 */
	onload() {
		// on loading the plugin
		this.statusBarTextElement = this.addStatusBarItem().createEl('span')
		this.statusBarTextElement.textContent = '0 lines';
		this.app.workspace.on('active-leaf-change', async () => {
			// read content of active file
			const file = this.app.workspace.getActiveFile();
			if (file) {
				const content = await this.app.vault.read(file);
				this.updateLineCount(content);
			}
		})
	}
}
```

Count the lines and update the status bar:

```typescript
	private updateLineCount(fileContent?: string) {
		const count = fileContent ? fileContent.split(/\n/).length : 0;
		const linesWord = count === 1 ? 'Zeile' : 'Zeilen';
		this.statusBarTextElement.textContent = `${count} ${linesWord}`;
	}
```

Count lines and update status bar when editing text:

```typescript
		this.app.workspace.on('editor-change', (editor) => {
			const content = editor.getDoc().getValue();
			this.updateLineCount(content);
		});
```

* Refactor code to read content and update status bar to private method, called also when plugin is loaded
!! Release a new version
* See [[Section in obsidian-sample-plugin|https://github.com/obsidianmd/obsidian-sample-plugin#releasing-new-releases]]
* Upload to git by: `git push`
* Tags must be uploaded separately:

 ```sh
 git push origin master --tags
```

